  "naissanceChecklistItem1Title": "Register baby for health insurance (3 months)",
  "naissanceChecklistItem1Desc": "You have 3 months after birth to register your child with a health insurer. If done within this period, coverage is retroactive from birth. After this deadline, there is a risk of coverage interruption. Compare child premiums between insurers — differences can be significant.",
  "naissanceChecklistItem2Title": "Apply for family allowances",
  "naissanceChecklistItem2Desc": "Apply through your employer (or your allowance office if self-employed). Allowances are paid from the month of birth. The amount depends on the canton (CHF 200 to CHF 305/month per child).",
  "naissanceChecklistItem3Title": "Report the birth to the civil registry",
  "naissanceChecklistItem3Desc": "The hospital usually transmits the announcement to the civil registry office. Verify that the birth certificate has been properly issued. You will need it for all administrative procedures.",
  "naissanceChecklistItem4Title": "Organize parental leave (APG)",
  "naissanceChecklistItem4Desc": "Maternity leave: 14 weeks at 80% of salary (max CHF 220/day). Paternity leave: 2 weeks (10 days), to be taken within 6 months. APG registration is done through your employer or directly with the compensation office.",
  "naissanceChecklistItem5Title": "Update the tax return",
  "naissanceChecklistItem5Desc": "An additional child entitles you to a tax deduction of CHF 6,700/year (LIFD art. 35). If you have childcare costs, you can deduct up to CHF 25,500/year. Remember to adjust your tax instalments for the current year.",
  "naissanceChecklistItem6Title": "Adapt the family budget",
  "naissanceChecklistItem6Desc": "A child costs on average CHF 1,200 to CHF 1,500/month in Switzerland (food, clothing, activities, insurance, nappies, etc.). Reassess your budget with the MINT Budget module.",
  "naissanceChecklistItem7Title": "Check pension planning (LPP and 3a)",
  "naissanceChecklistItem7Desc": "If you reduce your work rate, your LPP contributions decrease. Each part-time year means less capital at retirement. Consider compensating by contributing the maximum to the 3rd pillar (CHF 7,258/year).",
  "naissanceChecklistItem8Title": "Draft or update the will",
  "naissanceChecklistItem8Desc": "The arrival of a child changes the inheritance order. Children are forced heirs (CC art. 471). If you have a will, check that it respects the legal reserves.",
  "naissanceChecklistItem9Title": "Take out death/disability risk insurance",
  "naissanceChecklistItem9Desc": "With a dependent child, financial protection in case of death or disability becomes even more important. Check your current coverage (LPP, life insurance) and supplement if necessary.",
