  "mortgageStep4Subtitle": "Direct: you repay the bank each year (debt decreases, tax deduction decreases). Indirect: you pay into your 3a, then repay in a lump sum. Tax advantage of indirect.",
  "mortgageStep4Title": "Direct or indirect amortization?",
  "mortgageStep5Action": "Estimate your imputed rental value tax in MINT",
  "mortgageStep5Subtitle": "If you live in your property, you pay tax on the imputed rental value (fictitious rent). In return, you can deduct mortgage interest and maintenance costs.",
  "mortgageStep5Title": "What about imputed rental value?",
  "mortgageStep6Action": "Launch the Match Report in MINT",
  "mortgageStep6Subtitle": "A personal as much as financial decision. Factors: planned residence duration, professional stability, desired flexibility. Typical break-even: 7-12 years.",
  "mortgageStep6Title": "In the end: rent or buy?",
  "mortgageStep7Action": "Download the MINT purchase checklist",
  "mortgageStep7Subtitle": "Before signing: check co-ownership rules, building rating, planned works, renovation fund status. Have the deed of sale reviewed.",
  "mortgageStep7Title": "My action plan",
  "narrativeAmortizationBadge": "Amortization",
  "narrativeAmortizationBody": "Direct amortization reduces your debt each year. Indirect pays into a 3a, tax-deductible (OPP3). Depending on your marginal rate, indirect could cost you less overall.",
  "narrativeAmortizationHeadline": "Direct or indirect?",
  "narrativeBirthBadge": "Birth",
  "narrativeBirthBody": "Maternity leave (LAPG art. 16b–d) covers 14 weeks at 80% of salary. Family allowances vary by canton (LAFam art. 3). This simulator estimates the overall impact on your budget.",
  "narrativeBirthHeadline": "Birth costs and benefits",
  "narrativeCoverageBadge": "Insurance",
  "narrativeCoverageBody": "LAMal, daily allowance insurance, private liability, household insurance… Each insurance covers a different risk. This review identifies gaps based on your situation and canton.",
  "narrativeCoverageHeadline": "Check your coverage",
  "narrativeDisabilityBadge": "Disability",
  "narrativeDisabilityBody": "In case of disability, your income goes through 3 phases: employer (CO art. 324a), daily allowance insurance, then DI + LPP (LAI art. 28, LPP art. 23-26). The drop can reach 40-60% of your current salary.",
  "narrativeDisabilityHeadline": "Understand your disability gap",
  "narrativeEplBadge": "2nd pillar — EPL",
  "narrativeEplBody": "Art. 30c LPP allows you to withdraw your 2nd pillar to finance owner-occupied housing. Note: if you have made buy-backs, a 3-year lock period applies (LPP art. 79b para. 3).",
  "narrativeEplHeadline": "EPL withdrawal: benefits and 3-year lock",
  "narrativeFirstJobBadge": "First job",
  "narrativeFirstJobBody": "Between AVS (LAVS art. 5), LPP (art. 16), withholding tax and LAMal, your net is about 75-80% of gross. Understanding these deductions is the first step to good financial management.",
  "narrativeFirstJobHeadline": "Your first salary explained",
  "narrativeLibrePassageBadge": "Vested benefits",
  "narrativeLibrePassageBody": "When changing jobs, you have 6 months to transfer your LPP assets (LFLP art. 3). After this deadline, the capital is automatically deposited into a vested benefits account. Choose the right vehicle from the start.",
  "narrativeLibrePassageHeadline": "Vested benefits: 6 months to act",
  "narrativeMarriageBadge": "Marriage",
  "narrativeMarriageBody": "Marriage changes your taxation (LIFD art. 9), your matrimonial regime (CC art. 181) and your survivor benefits (LAVS art. 23, LPP art. 19). Depending on your respective incomes, the tax impact could be positive or negative.",
  "narrativeMarriageHeadline": "Financial impact of marriage",
  "narrativeRachatBadge": "2nd pillar",
  "narrativeRachatBody": "Spreading an LPP buy-back over several years allows you to deduct each instalment from taxable income (LPP art. 79b). Tax progressivity often makes this strategy more advantageous than a single payment.",
  "narrativeRachatHeadline": "Stagger to save",
  "narrativeRealReturnBadge": "3rd pillar",
  "narrativeRealReturnBody": "The displayed return doesn’t tell the whole story. After management fees and inflation, the real gain may differ. The 3a tax saving (LIFD art. 33) significantly improves the effective return.",
  "narrativeRealReturnHeadline": "Real return after inflation",
  "narrativeRetroactive3aBadge": "3rd pillar",
  "narrativeRetroactive3aBody": "From 2026, OPP3 art. 7 allows you to retroactively pay missed 3a contribution years. Each payment is deductible from taxable income (LIFD art. 33).",
  "narrativeRetroactive3aHeadline": "Catch up on up to 10 years of 3a",
  "narrativeSaronBadge": "Mortgage",
  "narrativeSaronBody": "SARON follows the money market and can change every quarter. A fixed rate locks in your interest for the entire term. Depending on your risk tolerance, the gap could work in your favour… or not.",
  "narrativeSaronHeadline": "SARON or fixed rate?",
  "narrativeUnemploymentBadge": "Unemployment",
  "narrativeUnemploymentBody": "The LACI provides compensation of 70-80% of insured earnings (art. 22). Duration depends on your contribution months and age (art. 27). This simulator estimates your rights based on your current situation.",
  "narrativeUnemploymentHeadline": "Your unemployment rights",
